nextPanel

private void nextPanel()
Change to the next frame. This requires testing to see if the button is enabled, returning if it is not, reenabling the back button if it was previously disabled, adding the Prev/Next panel if it is not the title screen, flipping the page, packing, and updating the buttons to enable/disable based on starts and stops.

prevPanel

private void prevPanel()
Change to the previous frame. This requires testing to see if the button is enabled, returning if it is not, reenabling the next button if it was previously disabled, flipping the page, packing, and updating the buttons to enable/disable based on starts and stops.

changePanel

private void changePanel(int index)
Change to an arbitrary frame. This requires testing to see if the index to change to is different than the current one, returning if it is not, adding the Prev/Next panel if it is not the title screen, flipping the page, packing, and updating the buttons to enable/disable based on starts and stops. This method performs checks to see if the index is within bounds.

Parameters:
index - the index to change to

checkButtons

private void checkButtons()
Updates the status of the buttons. If the current index is at a start, disable the previous button. If the current index is at a start, disable the next button. An index can be both at a start and a stop.

addQuestion

private void addQuestion()
Adds a new Question to the JList and to the backend. Increments the questionIndex to point to the new question, and increment the questionCount. Updates the buttons as necessary.

removeQuestion

private void removeQuestion()
Removes a Question from the JList and the backend. Decrements the questionIndex if necessary, at the end of the list, and decrement the questionCount. Updates the buttons as necessary.

moveUpQuestion

private void moveUpQuestion()
Moves a Question up the JList. Cannot move a question up that is at the beginning of the list.

moveDownQuestion

private void moveDownQuestion()
Moves a Question down the JList. Cannot move a question down that is at the end of the list.

updateQuestion

void updateQuestion(Question newQ)
Updates the question at the current index. This question was modified by the QuestionEditor. Make sure to update the type of question as well by creating a new one with the old properties.

Parameters:
newQ - the new question to add in the place of the old one
